 a world order. This fascinating account offers a new understanding of Captain Cook's voyages and how they affected the European world view.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aDiscoveries in geography. 0aDécouvertes géographiquesxEuropa. 0aVoyages around the worldxHistoryx18th century. 0aVoyages around the worldxHistoryy18th century. 0aVoyages autour du mondexHistoirex18e siècle. 7aHISTORY / Expeditions & Discoveries.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010z978311127416408iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010z978311127724008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertUniversity of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000z978311141860540uhttps://doi.org/10.59962/978077485156540uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780774851565423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780774851565/original  a978-3-11-127416-4  ACUP Complete eBook-Package Pre-2010b2010  a978-3-11-127724-0  ACUP Upgrade eBook-Package pre 2010b2010  a978-3-11-141860-5  University of British Columbia eBook-Package 2013-2000c2013d2000  aGBV-deGruyter-alles